      <profile-notes>Keywords: abuse of office
      People mentioned: Walter Chidhakwa
      Companies mentioned: Minerals Marketing Corporation of Zimbabwe
      Profile:
      Walter Chidhakwa, a former mines minister, appeared before a Harare magistrate court on December 21, 2017, the day after he was arrested by the Zimbabwe Anti-Corruption Commission on charges of criminal abuse of office. He was later released on bail. 
      The charges stemmed from the alleged non-compliance with the state-run Minerals Marketing Cooperation of Zimbabwe (MMCZ) Act which stipulated that the company board should have between six and 10 members whereas from December 2013 to December 2016 there was only one board member.</profile-notes>
